By providing a 'changelog_uri' in the metadata of the gemspec
a 'Changelog' link will be shown on https://rubygems.org/gems/bcrypt
which makes it quick and easy for someone to check on the changes
introduced with a new version.

commit.message:
Limit packaged files

Limit files included in the gem to the ones that are necessary.

This skips shipping the gem with directories such as `.github`, `spec` and other files that are not normally accessible and arguably should be skipped.

This saves us some bytes in transfer and disk space on all the computers these gems are downloaded to.

commit.message:
Add a test for passwords with null bytes

Raise an exception when passwords contain null bytes.  This was already
fixed (inadvertently I think?) in aec1265e.  StringValueCStr will raise
an exception if the string buffer it's unwrapping contains null bytes.

Fixes #115
Fixes #114

bad hashes on Linux. The original patch was incorrectly copying the
`data` struct into the string returned by the function.
